    "notes": "The Zero 2 W ships with either a CYW43436 or a CYW43430(b0) WiFi/BT combo chip depending on production revision; the brcmfmac driver probes the chip at runtime and requests firmware named '<base>-sdio.raspberrypi,model-zero-2-w.<ext>'. In RPi-Distro/firmware-nonfree these board-specific names are git symlinks, not distinct blobs: both the cyw43436 (43436) and cyw43430b0 chip IDs resolve to the SAME brcmfmac43436-sdio.* blob, while the plain cyw43430 (no b0) chip ID resolves to the separate brcmfmac43436s-sdio.* blob (which has no clm_blob — its calibration data is baked into the .bin). This manifest fetches the two underlying blob sets once each and records the alias filenames a board profile must create (as symlinks or copies) under /lib/firmware/brcm/ so whichever chip a given unit has, its firmware request resolves. Wiring these aliases into FirmwareFiles is deferred to gosd-3zrc (Board interface not implemented yet)."
